t falls back safely and still emits a valid plan artifact without corrupting other stored artifacts.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Needs implement fallback logic plus artifact store interaction to validate both output validity and non-corruption of other artifacts. Unit-only tests can miss unintended writes/deletes in persistence wiring. Rejected higher levels because behavior is deterministic fallback semantics with local artifact state, not real infra or model-quality dependent.","test_description":"Start with artifact store lacking `grounding` but containing unrelated artifacts; run implement-stage; assert `plan` is produced and schema-valid, unrelated artifacts are unchanged, and no spurious `grounding` mutation/corruption occurs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.66,"System":0.08,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.02}}]}
